U.S. Company to Invest 100 Million Dollars in Brazil 
The U.S. company Procter Gamble announced here today it would invest
100 million dollars in Brazil this year.
Procter Gamble president John Pepper unveiled the investment plan today
at a meeting with Brazilian President Fernando Henrique Cardoso.
The company intends to transform its depositary in Sao Paulo, Brazil
into its largest plant in Latin America, which produces dresses,
shampoo and hygienic products.
The investment, which may triple the company's production capacity in
Brazil, will create at least 300 new jobs.
